Product Description

RjKart Handcrafted Belt Lock Notebook Journal Leather Diary

It's an handmade Cardboard journal with beautiful cover. The journal is consisting of handmade Sketch papers (khadi papers). It's a refillable lock journal. Every page of this diary will become a gem with your precious memories.

Product Highlight

  • Product Dimension : 4*6 inches 120 gsm
  • Number of Pages: 144 pages & 72 sheets
  • Material: 100% Leather handmade Paper
  • Closure Type : Thread Closure

Keep Good Memories Alive

Perfect Daily Writing Journal

No need to mention of course that you can use it as a daily diary.If you are a writer, a poet, a comedian, or a fellow daydreamer, it is thebest place to note your novel ideas, best lyrics, witty two-liners, or dreamsfor the future.

Beautifully ​Handcrafted Cardboard Notebook

Our Cardboard notebook is made entirely by hand, with a simple handcrafted finish that makes each unique.The simple Cardboard cover is fitted with elastics along the spine that hold inserts to help you keep memories from your day to day life as you travel through the world.

Lay Flat Easy to Write

Lay Flat Design, you Can Write On Both Sides Of the Paper with Fountain pen without worrying ghosting bleed through problems.

Uses :

  • These Diaries Could Be Used For Sketching, Writing, Caligraphy, Personal Memos And Alot Of Other Writing And Gift Purposes.

Darshii
4.0 out of 5 stars Pretty good actually!
Reviewed in India on 27 September 2022
Colour: Design3Verified Purchase
This diary is of pretty good quality and the design is exactly what I wanted! I plan to journal my time in this diary as if I'm in the twenty one pilots lore, so this is perfect. I've already painted it and customized it.

The size is ideal for me (6x4 inches in lxb and 1.5 inches in height for 200 sheets) but it may be small for some people, and if you wish to try scrapbooking or painting then the paper is too thin to handle markers or any water-based or oil-based colour. You can use pen and pencil but the imprint will show up on the backside of the page as well as possibly the next page. Any glue used to paste on stickers or photos will crinkle up the sheet too unless used carefully.

The cover is soft, not leathery. It's very comfortable and light and you can carry it with you! The acrylic paint on the cover did not bleed through but it definitely is not waterproof. The binding is decent, it's bound with rope/string instead of glue and in multiple sections, sewn together. Some pages lay flat (like where sections separate or middle of a section) but the rest need a bit of spine cracking.

For the key and piercings (to hold the key pocket), real metal is used which has a bit of rust (which I personally like the look of) and the very first page has the rust stain, but luckily it works for what I plan to sketch on the first page. As you can see in the pictures, the strap for the key isn't long enough to wrap around and rest in its pocket fully so I adjusted it by wrapping it once and placing it in the pocket then pulling at the start to wrap around about halfway and tucked it in. It's kind of more secure this way too.

TL;DR:
Overall rating:
Design and Aesthetic - 5/5
Quality (cover, strap, key) - 5/5
Quality (paper) - 3/5
Quality (binding) - 4/5
Size - 4/5 (perfect for me but may be too small for some other people)
Material (cover) - 5/5
Material (paper) - 4/5
Portability (size) - 5/5
Portability (weight) - 4/5 (a little weighted but still very light)
Customizability (cover) - 4/5 (space constraint and soft, kind of uneven surface like felt or faux textured leather, if anything)
Customizability (paper) - 3/5 (quality constraint, can't stick things and paint freely, only good for sketching and writing which may leave an imprint on the next page(s) as well).

Thank you!
